

Memory Management by the Kernel ---

Memory ---RAM ---Main Memory ---Primary Memory---Volatile Memory!!!!

Memory is divided into 
kernel space ---OS processes, ready Q, IVT,ISR
User space -- our processes

1 byte of memory is assigned one address( hexadecimal )

memory address= is a hex number given to identify a location or a byte !!!


memory addresses --------
	1. physical address = address that identifies each RAM location of one byte .It starts from 1 upto for example upto 16GB RAM ( 16* 1000000000 )
	
	2. Logical address OR 	3. Offset address
	
	4. Base address
	5. Actual address




















